---
// AI workflows: four numbered value-prop cards + before/after agent
// transcript comparison. Anchor `#ai` is referenced from nav and footer.
//
// Per gspec/features/home-page.md §4 P0 "An AI-workflows section explains
// the tool's value for AI coding agents and demonstrates it with a
// before/after comparison."

import Kicker from './Kicker.astro';
---

<section id="ai" class="section ai accent-em" aria-labelledby="ai-heading">
  <div class="ai-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <header class="section-head">
    <Kicker label="Supercharge AI workflows" />
    <h2 id="ai-heading">
      Stop letting your agents <span class="accent">guess</span>.
    </h2>
    <p class="lede">
      AI coding tools are powerful — but only as good as the context you give
      them. A citadel is a single, current, structured corpus your agents can
      <em>actually</em> read.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="ai-grid">
    <article class="ai-card">
      <p class="ai-num">01</p>
      <h3>One folder. Whole system.</h3>
      <p>
        Point Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, or Antigravity at
        <code>citadel/</code> and the agent inherits architecture decisions,
        API contracts, and runbooks from every repo at once — not just the
        one it’s editing.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="ai-card">
      <p class="ai-num">02</p>
      <h3>Provenance you can trust.</h3>
      <p>
        Every directory carries a <code>.maester-source.json</code> marker —
        source URL, ref, commit SHA, sync time. When an agent quotes a doc,
        you can trace it back to its origin.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="ai-card">
      <p class="ai-num">03</p>
      <h3>Fresh by construction.</h3>
      <p>
        Run <code>maester sync</code> before any agent session — or wire it
        into CI. The corpus reflects the actual current state of every
        source, not last quarter’s snapshot.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="ai-card">
      <p class="ai-num">04</p>
      <h3>Selective, by contract.</h3>
      <p>
        Either the source publishes its own <code>maester.yaml</code>, or
        your citadel sends a <em>traveling maester</em> to do the publishing
        in its stead. Agents see the deliberately curated surface — not the
        noise of a full clone.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="before-after">
    <div class="ba-col ba-before">
      <header><span class="ba-tag err">without maester</span></header>
      <div class="ba-msg ba-user">
        <span class="ba-who">you</span>
        <p>Add rate limiting to the billing webhook handler.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-msg ba-bot">
        <span class="ba-who">agent</span>
        <p>
          I’ll add a token-bucket middleware. Where do you want the limits
          configured?
        </p>
        <p class="ba-hint">
          <span aria-hidden="true">›</span> agent doesn’t know your platform’s
          standard middleware, env-var conventions, or ADR-014 on retry
          policy. It guesses.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-col ba-after">
      <header><span class="ba-tag ok">with maester</span></header>
      <div class="ba-msg ba-user">
        <span class="ba-who">you</span>
        <p>Add rate limiting to the billing webhook handler.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-msg ba-bot">
        <span class="ba-who">agent</span>
        <p>
          Reading <code class="ac"
            >citadel/platform-runbooks/middleware.md</code
          > and
          <code class="ac">citadel/architecture-notes/adr-014-retry.md</code
          >…
        </p>
        <p>
          Using <code class="ac">@platform/limiter</code> at 100 req/min per
          tenant, matching ADR-014. Env var:
          <code class="ac">BILLING_WEBHOOK_RPS</code>. Adding the runbook
          entry too.
        </p>
        <p class="ba-hint">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> agent reads the citadel and applies
          the system’s actual conventions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .section {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 1180px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5.5rem 2rem;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .ai {
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .ai-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 4rem 0;
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(124, 231, 199, 0.03) 40%, transparent),
      radial-gradient(900px 500px at 70% 50%, rgba(177, 151, 252, 0.05), transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .section > * {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .section-head {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }
  .section-head h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.2vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .accent {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .ai-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .ai-card {
    position: relative;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.75rem 1.75rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .ai-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .ai-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.625rem;
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .ai-card p {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .ai-card code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--fg);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .before-after {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .ba-col {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--surface);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    min-height: 320px;
  }
  .ba-col > header {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.125rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--elevated);
  }
  .ba-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  .ba-tag.err {
    color: var(--danger);
  }
  .ba-tag.ok {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .ba-msg {
    padding: 1.125rem 1.375rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .ba-msg:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .ba-msg.ba-bot {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.012);
  }
  .ba-who {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--fg-faint);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  .ba-msg p {
    margin: 0 0 0.375rem;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .ba-msg p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .ba-msg code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
  .ac {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .ba-hint {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-top: 0.625rem !important;
    padding-top: 0.625rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border-strong);
  }
  .ba-before .ba-hint span {
    color: var(--danger);
  }
  .ba-after .ba-hint span {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .ai-grid,
    .before-after {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .section {
      padding: 4rem 1.375rem;
    }
  }
</style>
